node.text: Live your life now! It’s so easy to get caught up in our plans to “succeed” in the eyes of the world and we lose sight of the present moment. The gift. I can lose track of what really makes me actually happy sometimes. I think we should do that first, and the rest will follow. The rest of your life, or like Billy Joel sings, “Vienna”, will wait for you! So feed the inner child first. I think that voice is smarter than we give it credit. Because when it’s all said and done, you can get what you want or you can just get old.. 🤍

node.text: The Pretty Grit, this project we’ve  been working on for over a year, it came out of a place of real pain. A deep hurt I hadn’t felt in life before. I started a band and this was the first song we wrote. The Pretty Grit is about flipping your circumstances. Taking something so gritty and shitty and turning it into something beautiful. And that’s really what art means to me, personally. That’s Pretty Grit. I’m so excited to set out on this journey with my five brothers @theprettygrit @cocoonmalibu GO WATCH THE WHOLE ACOUSTIC SET ON YOUTUBE LINK IN BIO🙏🏼🖤💛🎸🥁🎷✌🏼🎶

node.text: Applaud Our Kids raises money to get kids free music lessons! By making a donation of $5 you not only give back to this great cause but you also get access to the online concert October 22nd. I’m performing!! Comment on this video for more donation info 🤟🏼 @applaudourkidsfoundation

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jack Griffo in Los Angeles, California with @ryanunderfire, @theglamjew, @chantzsimpson, @terrycharliemike, @blakeleebergman, @brennenevans, @erik.arbouet, and @sylviavanhoeven. May be an image of 2 people and indoor.

node.text: Isn’t it ironic! This imperfect perfection. A society driven by judgment, shame, comparison and cancel culture. Nobody is perfect, not even one. I get so caught up in being right sometimes that I lose myself.. it’s unnerving. I make mistakes often. I try my best to learn from them. Thank you to those close to me who give me breaks, cut me slack, and lovingly provide perspective. Slow to speak. Quick to listen 💭

node.text: What a waste of a life to be anyone else but yourself. What a slap in the face to your own literal self! I mean here we are with a life on this earth, not a dog or a bird or a plant. While these beings are also good and worth being created and I’m sure would be a dope life to live, we are just blessed and lucky to be out here as a HUMANs!! With deep emotion, an able mind capable of great intelligence, a durable body; an actual SPACESUIT we’re born with attached to our bones and organs, holding our very soul within it. What a gift. We’re able to learn, grow, fail, to succeed. I have all this yet still at times bow down to another, living a life they want me to live. What a slap in the face. I’ve done it too many times man. Be yourself. No apologies.

node.text: Friends & dogs & music🫀 the purest parts of life 🌎 every day I get older and as the time seems to pass faster, it’s these photos that remind me of what’s important and what you might take with you when ur gone from here. It’s connection with people, relationships, sharing in community with music and learning how to love yourself well enough to get out of your own way and love people better, and make the world better just cuz u were here.. 🌈

node.text: YO kids. I’m checking in with u, the old gram. Here’s the rundown. I’m here. Im good. Life’s just been a bit uncomfy.. in a good way? I guess being comfortable isn’t all it’s cracked up to be. Covid made me uneasy for sure. Down was up left was right and we didn’t know when it would end. I pretty much ran out of acting work, which made me SUPER uncomfy. The death of both my grandparents, the separation of my best friends in the entire world, my parents. My life got super uncomfy super quick. But after wrestling with it for the past year, I’m finally grateful for the  discomfort. Since Thundermans ended in 2018 I had been writing a small collection of songs. I felt like I finally had the time and energy to explore music the way I always wanted to. It was going good, but the songs weren’t anything special. It wasn’t until the discomfort; when everything got all shook up, and these more challenging times both in my career and my personal life came, that the songs became special to me. I started writing stuff I actually gave a damn about. I had passion again. I never pursued music until now cuz I knew If I didn’t have anything to say it would be cheap and just so meaningless. So I started a band and we’re releasing some of our songs very soon. And that’s UNCOMFY. Hah.. but i wouldn’t have it any other way. Maybe they’ll help you thru a hard time, or maybe you’ll just like to jam to them in the car. Both are most acceptable. The songs are of love, loss, blessings, despair and the beauty in nature. Among other things. 💋
